narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about how the different parts of the world took different paths of development in the last couple of centuries. I gained a global perspective on problems of development, and learned to identify situations and policies that are likely to prioritize growth.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The material was broad but also analyzed at a deeper level - the coverage of the course was the perfect amount. The course should stay as is.
No improvement necessary, one of the best courses at Yale!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes - it provides a great overview of economic development through a historical lens
